TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hagerty, Kathleen
T1  - Equilibrium Bid-Ask Spreads in Markets with Multiple Assets
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297966
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 2
SP  - 237
EP  - 257
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - The paper models the specialist system as a monopolistically competitive market. The demand for the asset is found by solving the investor's portfolio problem with transactions costs. These demand equations are used as inputs in the specialist's price-setting problem. It is shown that equilibrium prices and hence equilibrium portfolio holdings depend upon the characteristics of the assets and the investors and the number of assets being traded. Conditions are given under which the bid and ask prices will converge to the competitive level as the number of assets increases. Predictive differences between a monopolistically competitive market and a market where specialists collude are also discussed.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297966
ER  - 



