T1  - Delegation Games in Customs Unions
PY  - 1991
Y1  - 1991/04/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297974
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 58
IS  - 2
SP  - 391
EP  - 397
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We study a model in which a customs union trades with countries which behave strategically. Provided that the members of the customs union are similar but not identical, we show that both in the case in which intra-union transfers are allowed as well as in the one in which they are not, one country may want to delegate authority for making union policy to its partner. The delegation decision depends on whether the policies used by union and non-union countries are strategic substitutes or complements, and on which union member is more “aggressive”.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297974
ER  - 



